1 f. Administer grants to county , regional, or tribal correctional facilities; and
2 g. Provide annual reports to the department of corrections and rehabilitation
3 regarding the status of the correctional facility grant program.
4 2. The correctional facility grant committee shall administer a grant program to expand
5 access to evidence-based programming in county , regional, and tribal correctiona l
6 facilities.
7 3. Grants awarded under this section must prioritize county , regional, or triba l
8 correctional facilities with no existing re-entry, educational, counseling, or other
9 evidence-based programs. Grants may be awarded to support access to culturally
10 responsive treatment alternative programs.
11 SECTION 2. AMENDMENT. Section 12-47-31 of the North Dakota Century Code is
12 amended and reenacted as follows:
13 12-47-31. Discharge of offenders - Clothing - Transportation.
14 1. The department of corrections and rehabilitation, in coordination with the department
15 of transportation, shall facilitate a process for offenders applying for photo
16 identification, including a driver's license, nondriver identification card, temporary
17 driver's license, or temporary nondriver identification card.
18 2. The department of corrections and rehabilitation shall provide an offender released
19 from the department appropriate clothing and transportation to a reasonable point as
20 specified in the release plan, based upon need.
21 3. The department of corrections and rehabilitation, in cooperation with the department of
22 health and human services, shall connect all eligible offenders to Medicaid assistance
23 or other health and human services programs before the offender is released from the
24 department.
25 SECTION 3. A new section to chapter 27-02 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
26 and enacted as follows:
27 Supreme court mitigation of racial disparity - Report to legislative management .
28 The supreme court shall provide an annual report to the legislative management regarding
29 efforts to mitigate racial disparities in the state court system identified by the minority justice
30 implementation committee, and implemented by the supreme court.
